<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880414-0085 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Texas Industries Gives Forward Added Post At Cement Division </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TXI WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> DALLAS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Texas Industries Inc. said Gordon E. Forward, president and chief executive officer of the Chaparral Steel Co. unit, was named to the additional position of president of the cement/concrete division.    Mr. Forward assumes the responsibilities of Fergus Walker, executive vice president and chief operating officer, who has become a consultant to the company. Mr. Walker left his position &quot;by mutual agreement&quot; with management, the company said. His titles won't be filled.    Mr. Walker couldn't be reached for comment.    A spokesman said Mr. Forward was given additional responsibilities because he has been successful in building a flourishing specialty steel company while other steel concerns have struggled. The cement division accounts for about $270 million of this cement and steel concern's $640 million in annual revenue. </TEXT></DOC>